values:
I think this is a god over-a-year-lapsed-between part 2 to my last LJ entry. 

Brandon & I broke up &, as always, I have to find the perfect song to describe how I feel. Just found it:


Maria Taylor - Lady Luck

 We were the words that washed from the sand - I still prayed we wouldn't give it up.
 We were the wings of a hummingbird, but I grew tired as I would wait for Lady Luck.
 
 We were the blue in the newborn's eye - I still prayed we could keep it up.
 We were the view from my childhood room, but I grew wise as I would look for Lady Luck.
 
 We were the wear in my favorite shirt, I still prayed we could make it work.
 We were the lair for the baby cubs, but I grew strong as I prepared for Lady Luck.
 
 And follow yourself & hope that you know where your going,
&don't question your steps that lead you into the morning.
 And you'll meet a friend along the way. You can't wait for each new day.
 It doesn't always work the way you planned it. I like it better this way.
 
It's lady luck.

Some things are too good. Some things are pretty bad.

I smashed a full soda over my boyfriend's head & whilst balling for an extended & being told that I'll be loved no matter what, I decided to take my bipolar medication again. MISTAKE. Then I suffered from withdrawal for several days & haven't slept a full night since, but things are looking up.

Speaking of my boyfriend, I totally don't believe in happily ever after, so why have things been so amazing? Can you quit reading my mind all the time & making me love you so much? ps. I still can't trust you because of the past.


NO job. No money. Wish I was better at school.

This is immature, I guess.
i just found out what brandon, john & i's "seasons" are! john is a summer. i am a spring & brandon is a winter. LET'S BUY NEW CLOTHES AND MAKE UP.

i'm back to my old ways: throwing fits, being in love, never sleeping, devoting my spare time to art & writing, internet addiction, & partying.

i guess i can't change who i am?

WHAT'S GOING ON RIGHT NOW?


i'm eating cottage cheese & drinking soda & making an azure ray/ maria taylor "best of" mix cd. & getting everything ready to spend all night making drawing and painting ON PAPER. instead of my usually knit fabrics.

i've been writing a lot lately, too. nothing too special, 3 page long proses about your heart bloodying up my papers as it rolls around in my book bag.

i want to run & dance & scream & roll around in large patches of soft green grass in the middle of parks while los campesinos! is playing loudly around us. where is that music even playing from? it's like we're in a movie. "oh, maybe we're in a movie!" i think that's it!
i want you to tape the pages of the silly asian cartoon stationary i've sent you all over your dorm room walls. they can flutter around in response to my exaggerated body movements. even sweaty & cramped next to you in your twins sized bed, i'm smiling.
i always end up walking away with a good feelings, yeah it's definitely a movie.






the opposite of true love is as follows:

REALITY!

i don't feel like talking to anyone or really doing anytihng other than art & school. my sister is in town & we are kind of bff, so i have to hang out with her for hours everyday. i mean, i want to, but i mainly want to be a hermit. when i do talk, i just want to talk about my boyfriend.

i'm taking an online history class. 3 exams, 5 quizzes, 5 discussion board topics, & 2 papers in three weeks. BUT I DON"T HAVE TO DRIVE 15 MINUTES TO SCHOOL EVERYDAY!

ohohoh, & on amazon.com someone rated out book like this:

Liberal Rag-DROP CLASS!!, February 28, 2008
I had to purchase this book for a college class or I would have promptly returned it. The liberal bias presented in this text, and the photos, is nothing short of shameful. The book stands as a testament to what is wrong with education today. While Presidents Ford, Reagan, and both Bushs are largely ignored, the Clintonistas are pictured throughout the text...gag me with a fork!

i haven't had a job in like a month, but i'm been keeping so busy & i've been super happy, until i look at my bank account, then i realize i'm being a dumbass. here's my day, it goes like this:

11:00am - wake up
12:30pm - go to the grocery store with my grama
1:30pm - go job hunting
3:00pm- sign up for the summer 2 class i'm taking
5:00pm - yoga class at the ymca
7:00pm - abs class at the ymca

please throw in endless interneting, too. & i'm been writing a lot & telling myself that i think it's really good.

AFRAID MY HEART, IT BEATS TOO SLOW
OR THAT I DIED & JUST DIDN'T KNOW
OR OF A FATE I WILL HAVE TO CHOOSE, &
I'M AFRAID OF HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU.

there's just a time when we must all let go - of the breath that we hold.

i've been trying to be really confident lately. it's working out really badly.
the only way i can think of gaining confidence is to pretend to be confident, then i figured if i pretended long enough it would just happen.
so i just feel like embarrassed all the time & like i'm behind this thick shell crying.
idk, i want to cry like all the time. i feel like crying right now & i don't even know why.
i'm trying to feel pretty, too. ugh, this is too hard. idk, i convinced myself that my boyfriend & all my friends & everyone else hates me. i guess that's really unhealthy.


I CAN BE SHY & HAVE REALLY LOW CONFIDENCE.
I CAN SEPARATE MYSELF FROM EVERYONE.
I AM GOING TO GO CRY IN MY ROOM RIGHT NOW & THAT'S FINE, TOO.

i saw maria taylor live like a week ago & in the encore they talked her into playing "two of those too." she said she hadn't played it in over two years. she played it so shakily & she kept forgetting the lyrics, but i felt so lucky to be hearing it.

it's about how she moved to athens, georgia. it's her most beautiful lyrics, i think.

AND YOU CAN'T SUSTAIN ANYTHING
EVERYTHING MUST CHANGE
AND BE THANKFUL FOR EVERYTHING
AND I AM
I AM
I AM
WHY DOESN'T ANYONE THINK MY PURPLE BOYFRIEND IS HOT?

Jona Bechtolt
(i wanna tour the world with you & dance around to yr macbook & make videos & be vegan)
 
Conor Oberst
(plz get back on drugs & wander around new york too high to function with me & let me sing backing vocals in yr songs)

Khaela Maricich
(let's make art all day & you can help me with my poetry & we can kiss & hold hands so sweetly)

Wes Anderson
(we can have the weirdest talks & do the most random, spur-of-the-moment things)

Michael Cera
(we can be really awkward in public together & i will go to all your band's shows & post a link to your internet tv show on my myspace)


Brandon Woodward
(i will take pix of you at your bball game when you turn strangely purple, then post them on the internet)

i actually had a really bad day. woke up feeling sick,
went over to brandon's house around 11am & napped for like an hour,
then we went to guitar center where he bought a bunch recording stuff.
i wanted to which wich really badly, but we went to gyros instead & ate really crappy falafel.
i got my mustache waxed.
we went back to brandon's where he set up his equipment
while i addressed all his graduation thank you letters,
then when i was done i just sat there while fiddled with his stuff until 4pm,
then we left with his little brother to their hair appointments
& i did sudoku while they got hair cuts.
then we went back to brandon's & i kind of had high hopes for hanging outs,
but he just recorded a bunch of stuff & made a lot of adjustments while i sat there.
i was really bored & hungry, & i didn't want to interrupt what he was doing,
so i just went home & made myself dinner.
then my grama & i watched 'the glass house' while i ate.
that was deff the best part of my day. it ended like 15 minutes ago.
now i have to go back to brandon's because i'm going to go watch him play a basketball game.
probz one of the most boring days ever.

"In your profile, you wrote the following:

"i'm in love! it's one of those crazy, all-over-the-place, way too passionate, but always falling short kind of loves that you have to constantly doubt & never really feel all the way good about it. oh, but when your body is next to my body, all those horrible unforgivable things you always do to me seem so forgivable.."

That is one of the best descriptions of love I have EVER come across...

very insightful...

just my two cents

-R"



some 33 year old guy from arlington thinks i'm a love expert. okcupid always be saying i'm some kind of love & sex expert. i guess for my age i kind of am.


oh yeah, i got fired today.

looks like i haven't slept again
stupid shitty boyfriend who doesn't give a shit about me

"no need to argue" is my official break up album. i don't know if that's really sad or not, but i totally thought to myself today "time to download no need to argue."

my sister was telling me about the girl she explosively decided she was in love with in a short amount of time & how she wanted to move across the country & make all these plans & completely change her whole life for this really fragile thing. & i said she should. i said everyone should live there life that way & that it's the way i plan to live mine. so i was doing it. i was moving from texas, the only place i've ever lived, to rhode island because i found a school i loved, but it's like you didn't have something to do with it.

i was upset by the fact that i had not cried in months, despite being very sad. now the mood swings are back! the crying, then the too-happy, the loving, the hating. OMG what a terrible lj entry!


well, i got a BLACKJACK & it's has a better camera than my actually camera so i'm pretty excited. & i got a new jobs being a host as bjs brewhouse in arlington. it's pretty boring, but i'm not hating on $8.50 an hour. i mean, i'm not happy about it either.

maybe it has something to do with current personal life? idk! i've been watching so many videos & having longings & stuff! i'm never like this!

here they are in order: (i'll add more as i think of them)

1 MICHAEL CERA



2 WES ANDERSON




3 BECK

i gotz my wisdom teeth out. shit, was EASY. i got there at 8am. i went in at 8:10. they put the iv in my that kind of hurt, but nowhere near as much as when i used to have to get these really painful shots in my face every two weeks, for a year after my car accident. i slept on & off until 5pm, which suxed. just because every time i would wake up & want to do something, my grama would come bring me a pill that would make me pass out 20 minutes later.

i really don't want to eat, though! i'm not nauseous or anything because i got a pill for that, but the thought of food entering my food, is not pleasing. i will sip hot tea all day & be happy. ugh, i can't believe i was worried about this!

i wish i hadn't gotten excited about spring break. i'm actually really upset.

once i threw a sleepover & no one came. i decorated my apartment & made cupcakes & bought a lot of beer & food. then i just got sadder & sadder as i sat there alone, then cried all night.

that's how always feel now. always. i don't even know what that feeling is!  it's just the same though.


the most fun i had all week was last night. i  went to this vegan buffet in korean town, then played rock band, then saw no country for old men at the dollar theater.

when i woke up i saw that someone had called me last night to see what i was doing & i left my phone at home. & i forgot about a party i really would have gone, too! i'm so out of the loop. it's not possible to get back in, & finding a new loop failed, too.

i talk to brandon a lot.

he makes things for me.

i'll take yr "heartbroke" & i'll one up you a "your birthday present." i can't stop hating you & i don't think it's possible for me to ever love anyone else. at least not for a long fucking time. & yr new girlfriend looks like my sister & that is weird. & you can eat meat & not care about the state of the world together.

still i wonder how you are;
& what became of all of this.
did you cry when winter's hands
stole you from that fertile grave?
did your mother hold you dear
to ease the burden of your pain?
swallowed out into the light -
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

still i wonder how you are;
& how you ever came to be.
i was nothing but a hole,
you nestled in and fell asleep.
were you sad when you awoke?
torn away from fertile dreams
i didn't want to wake you up.
i'm still sorry. HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

DO YOU WONDER HOW I AM
OR WHATEVER BECAME OF ME?
do you envision my thin face
where the beaten go to drink?
I DIDN'T WANT TO CUT THAT CORD.
YOU SUCKED THE LIFE RIGHT OUT OF ME.
DO YOU REGRET CHOICES YOU'VE MADE?
i guess i was a mistake.
i guess i was a mistake.
i guess i was a mistake.
I GUESS I'M YOUR BIG MISTAKE.
well happy birthday anyway.
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

<i>It's not that bad
Not worse than you thought
He'll always come back as the man you dropped
He'll never come back as the man you loved</i>

i thought i'd at least like living in arlington, but i don't know anyone here. i don't have a job here. i need to hang out with annie more, but that situation is so strained. it just feels weird, because like six months ago, i lived in irving & i drove to arlington like 1-3 times a week because every friend i had lived in arlington. being the only one under 21 in a group of people was pretty alienating, but i had a 23-year-old boyfriend anchoring me in, but without him, it's dumb to think anyone would want to hang out with a 20-year-old, who throws tantrums & really has nothing to offer. even when i went to this gift-exchange over christmas, i got a present that was stuff for someone who has an apartment, then realized i'm a loser who lives in her uncle's spare bedroom, left early, was followed by my exboyfriend, who got into my car as i was trying to leave, then preceded the beg me together back together with him for like an hour, which just turned into a screaming match, then i just went to my sister's house & cried while holding me dog all night. i'm not a valuable asset to any social gorup. 

if not being 21 isn't hard enough, dating someone two years younger than me has made me a leper. idk, everything is so weird. yesterday he said to me, "do you think i'm really mature for my age?" & i said no. then he asked why i would want to date him then. UGH BECUASEZ we're strangely the same person & everything stupid & immature about him is really easy to forgive because i've been the same way & i've pretty much gotten over it. idk, the way he's such a people-pleaser & let's people be mean to him all the time, which is, of course, the reason people are mean to him. i just try to be nice to him all the time & he really needs that. it's nice to be needed. & it feels dumb to put all my efforts towards someone who is leaving in six months, but if a year is all we get, i'll make the best of it. i'll try to fight less, even though we haven't gone on a date in two weeks! i feel like i was allowed to be upset about it?

after gerardo & i broke up, my theory of everyone i ever cared about in my whole life has left me, seemed super confirmed, but my sister moved back into town to become somewhat of a confidant, my long-lost highschool boyfriend, first true love blah-blah, has turned years of on & off silence  into one of the best friendships i've ever had & i guess ida visits on holidays.

oh, & i had another job interview & didn't get the job. WAHWAHWAH

FIRST DAY OF CLASS, how i was dreading you! but it really wasn't that bad. i got here at 7:25am, which was way too early. patterns lab from 8-10:45am, but i worked until 11:55. then had tailoring lab from noon to 2:45, but worked until 3:30, then when back to the patterns lab to work until like 5 minutes ago. i'm glad i was able to get back into the swing of things! no one else seemed to, i spent like 2-3 hours alone in the labs today. how is anyone going to be ready for the assignment due wednesday at 8am?

i thought i was kind of out-of-control for a while, but not anymore. i just want to get fucked up & never sleep. & i think that's fine. FINE

i've been pretty carefree. carefree means irresponsible, i think.

i've been dating a new boy, but writing about him in my lj feels like cheating on gerardo somehow. not being with gerardo is starting to not feel strange. i still want to call him at the office in the middle of the day & make drunken party appearances with him & fall back on him as a constant when i fell myself doubting everything else, but i guess i've stopped doubting myself so much.

IDK.

oh, i live at my uncle's house in arlington. a six year old lives here part time, too.

i've lived in five cities now. two counties. still one state. 3 cities in the last six months.

i want to plant my feet!

i have about two boxes filled with stuff & a dresser full of clothes with me. about a third of my stuff stacked in a spare bedroom at ida's house, about half of my stuff in my gramparents' attic & the rest is on loan to my sister, because i can't really use it. she has my dog/soul mate, too.

it's pretty empty feeling, but i'm pushing through more than effectively. if empty means divided & small.

i'm working 40 hours/ 6 days a week at eight dollars an hour. WHY AM I DOING THAT? good usually outweighs bad & if it doesn't, you just have to wait a little while.

i was really happy in dallas. or i was as close as possible.

i'm working a shitty retail job that is 45 minutes away from where i am currently sleeping. & i make that drive 6 days a week.

it's 5 minutes away from my school, so i might keep it.

i think a lot of people aren't grateful for the things they have, but i think i'm not one of those people. plus a week ago i told my grampa i didn't have enough money to pay for my spring classes & he handed me his debit card.

as i get older the more i realize that some people just aren't meant to be happy, or pretty, or rich, or have a lot of friends, or lots of things, but the more i realize that, the more i realize that that doesn't even matter. i'm meant to wake up, to work, to go to school, to see the handful of people who do not find me annoying, to go to sleep. i don't know, the world just needs some kind of balance. there's no reason to be sad, really. i'm not even twenty, yet. maybe being sad at twenty won't seem so lame. no, it's probably will. i might have to wait until i'm thirty.
FIVE DAYS LEFT OF THIS SEMESTER. i'm not even excited, just SCARED.

i'm not as big as i thought i was. since i can be divided back into boxes & suitcases & trash bags full of clothes. since i can't stand alone, mainly monetarily, but i get so lonely, too.

but i'm too big to fit into other people's lives. spare bedrooms aren't meant to house people for more than a few days, i guess.

school is so fast. it's cold downtown because the buildings won't let the sunlight hit the sidewalk.


it's an infinite coincidence,
but it doesn't form a plan.
so, I'm headed for new england
or the paris of the south.
gonna find myself somewhere to level out

all this death must need a counterweight,
always someone born again.
first a mother bathes her child,
then the other way around.
the scales always find a way to level out

i just picked out my schedule for next semester. early registration is on the 20th at 12pm & i will be there at 12:35pm (because that's what i get out of class) this semester still has 4 or 5 major projects left & lots of late nights, stress eating & chilling dancing & singing to the pop stations in the lab after hours in between drafting, cut & sewing. BUT LET'S JUST GET EXCITED ABOUT WHAT'S TO COME!

a lomography camera,
turntables,

WILL SOMEONE PLZ MOVE TO DALLAS & LIVE WITH ME?






also, people are on-the-constant making comments about my weight gain. i don't think weighing 130 & being 5'2" is really that bad! i just don't wear it well, i guess. i want to be 115, again, but i'm seriously not doing anything about it!!!!!

at the library downtown. not in class! not worrying abot not being in class.

today i am cleaning out my car & finishing up my homework.
tonight i am going to a halloween party,
then seeing saw 4 at midnight.
tomorrow i am going to school until 6pm,
then attending the feminist book club my sister & i started.
then, i'm going to annie's halloween party, & getting 2wasted.
saturday morning i am having a garage sale,
then i'll probably sleep the rest of the day,
& i find somewhere to get wasted later that night.
sunday i plan to study & clean my house.

time is moving so quickly & i can't check up. i hate my 'textiles' & 'color theory application' classes. patterns is awesome, but i spent more than 20 hours a week on a four-hour class. i spend less time working!

last night i couldn't sleep & kept crying all night. i could think of the reason, but i think it had something to do with songs i miss & a lot to do with not letting myslef feeling sad for the last two months.

i don't care if i drink everyday. if i drinhk coffee everyday. if i eat ice cream everyday. eevverrrday yeah evv verday day yeah everydayy

i've become an expert at avoiding any mention or outward emotion pertaining to the recent ending of my three year relationship. i feel strange for many reasons. one, it was me who ended it & i never thought i would; two, it's me who is refusing to reconcile; three, it's me who's living alone & spending so much time alone; four, it's me who is terrible at dating (you're so good. you never like anyone, don't mind embarrassing yourself & can stand being around idiots for the sake of getting around)

times are strange. i'm def transferring to a university next fall. not texas women's university, like i planned, either. not that my life is only mine, i'm doing something crazy with it. new england, i hope. i'm going to start applying soon.

school work is tuff. i wish i was tuffer!

i'm actually doing pretty good in school.
i'm actually working 40 hours a week & not dying.
i'm actually having a pretty kickin' social life.
i'm kind of taking care of my house & my body. i could be eating a little better & sleeping a little more!

but i'm pretty damn proud of myself.

I LOVE

my super single attitude (MEFIRSTMEFIRSTMEFIRST)
going to school (ICAN'TEVENBELIEVEI'VELEARNEDSOMUCH)
my dog (YOUSTINKBUTYOUCURLINMYARMSASWEFALLASLEEPANYWAYS)
my job (IFITWASN'T35MINUTESAWAY&NOTGIVINGMEENOUGHMONEYMAYBE)


pretty much all i need is like $50,000 & everything would be perfect.

if i could have anything, other than an abundance of money so i could go to school all the time,


i would want a tiny camera. i have two cameras, one that is tiny, but kind of broken & one that is huge. ugh. i think ill gave to stick to the huge one! i need memories!

i wake up alone, then go to school. at school i'm finally making friends. slowly, but that's the way to do it.
i come home to an empty home to watch tv, play with my puppy, do homework, endlessly talk on the phone.
at nights i work, sore feet & too small tips & too long of hours, but i keep smiling.
i come home to an empty house again, make time for friends, make time for me, so no one gets lost.
everything is fine & i'm happy.

1) make a B or higher in all of my classes,
2) become friends with lots of fashion society of el centro members,
3) always pay my bills & not struggle,
4) party like crazy,
5) work like crazy,
6) drink & dance like crazy,
7) have super hot trophy boyfriend, preferably naive with disposable income,
8) find a roomate.

FALL 2007, here i come!

i just moved yesterday. even though i live in an area i'm not really familiar with, oak cliff already feels like home. when i get a better fan & my water turned on it def will. g2g tomorrow is the first day of school!

i missed my bus! i hate how buses com every 15 minutes during rush hour, but only once an hour during th afternoon. well, i love in the morning i can take the 7:15, (if i'm way early) 7:30, (if i want to be 10 minutes early) 7:45, (if i want to be 10 minutes late) 8:00 (my regular bus) 8:15 (if i want to be way late) 8:30 (if i want to be embarrassingly late) 8:45, 9:15, 9:30 (yeah, i think i've taken 'em all! but n the after noon i can only take the 11:20, 12:20, or 1:20. ugh, this is my first time taking the 1:20. my watch said 12:22 when i got to the bus stop! the bus driver is usually a total bitch & harasses everyone before she let's them on the bus, too, so it's usually kind of late.

ugh.

school was actually kind of terrible today. i didn't go yesterday so i was kind of behind/ i came early & stayed late to make up for it, but i'm still screwed. i believe i spent a total of 12-13 hours working on it, like in class/on the bus/at home, then the next assignment i turned in today, i only spent 6 hours working on it. she said it was so bad she would not accept it & i had to completely re-do it this weekend. so i have two sketches to do instead of one. i don't work sunday, so all day will homeworkhomework.

um in other news.

i like how gerardo likes to keep our apartment clean. like, he makes me do my share & always makes me feel like crap for making messes & asking for his help & stuff, but i actually have to do stuff & maybe feeling like crap will make me change my ways. it's been 10 months of living otgeter & i'm so much better all ready. it can only go up from here. that's my motto "it can only go up from here!" dang it, i think that's rilo kiley lyric. yeah,

& i feel like a million bucks today, a million bucks today,
cause i know it can only go up from here,
 cause she says it's so much better after all.
 after all we been through,
i can't get my mind off of you.
it's a hell of a way to spend the whole day through.

i'm a coffee addict! isn't that weird? well, it is if you knew i've always thought coffee was gross even though i had never really tried it until less than a month ago. i work at a brazilian coffee house! kind of, it's really just a brazilian-inspired restaurant with a big coffee bar. i don't even like those fancy flavored coffees, i like 16 ounces of plain, black coffee with two sweet n lows. guys, don't expect me to go through a starbucks drive thru with you to pick up $4 1000-calorie coffee drinks. 


my day if i was responsible:

 6:15: wake up & take shower
6:45: make myself breakfast & leave the house
7:45: get off train, pick up coffee & be in class by 8am
12:00: leave class & work on homework
1:45: arrive at work for 2pm shift
11:00: leave work & go straight to bed when i get home


my actual day:

7:00: wake up, shove my stuff together & make breakfast
7:15: leave house, then do homework on the train
8:15: get coffee, stroll into my 8am class at 8:30
11:30: leave class to read in the library
12:30: nap on library couch
1:30: wake up & catch train
2:05: arrive at work for 2pm shift
11:00 leave work & go home, hang out with gerardo
12:30 fall asleep
